section.div: Computational science Postdoc at Argonne National Laboratory working on applying machine learning to simulations in lattice QCD.
A simple way to jot down notes
A python API for Lattice QCD applications

Tuplex is a parallel big data processing framework that runs data science pipelines written in Python at the speed of compiled code. Tuplex has similar Python APIs to Apache Spark or Dask, but rather than invoking the Python interpreter, Tuplex generates optimized LLVM bytecode for the given pipeline and input data set.
